{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Peanut Milk","content":["Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in peanuts. Remove bowl from lid, cover with water then set aside to soak for approx. 8 hours.","Strain peanuts through a sieve, discarding water.","Place reserved soaked peanuts and water in mixing bowl then heat <nobr>15 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Leave to stand for 5 minutes then chop <nobr>1 min\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Strain mixture through a muslin cloth set over a jug, squeezing to ensure all liquid is removed. Reserve peanut pulp in muslin (see tip). Transfer liquid in jug to a sterilised glass bottle and set aside in fridge. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Pancakes","content":["Place linseeds in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>15 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add oats and grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add bananas, oil, honey, 360 g reserved peanut milk and baking powder then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Heat a little oil in a pancake or frying pan over a medium heat. Pour a small ladle of batter into the centre and fry for 2-3 minutes or until bubbles appear on the surface of pancake. Flip pancake and fry for 1 minute, then transfer to a plate and keep warm. Repeat until all batter is used.","Serve with fresh berries and honey."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Peanut Milk","content":["130 g peanuts, roasted, unsalted","1000 g water, plus extra for soaking"]},{"title":"Pancakes","content":["20 g linseeds","240 g oat flakes","140 g bananas, cut in pieces","30 g groundnut oil, plus extra for frying","15 g honey, plus extra for serving","1 tsp baking powder","mixed fresh berries, for serving"]}],"id":"r134367","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-OkJpo_l_OXU\/XZanoFwt3KI\/AAAAAAAAhB0\/xvAarscTAGIkFkv9rEk6msVXR9Qo6XR-wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Op3dzMN6wAQm5paf.png","title":"Oat Pancakes with Peanut Milk","publishedAt":"2018-02-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"6 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"17 g","calories":"570 kJ \